Pre-Game Insights: Congo DR maintained their perfect start to the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers on September 9 with a 2-0 victory over Ethiopia.
Tanzania picked up their first win in the AFCON qualifying race last time out, fighting back from behind to secure a 2-1 victory over Guinea.
Sebastien Desabre's men have now gone three consecutive games without defeat across all competitions, claiming three wins and one draw.
Hemed Suleiman's men have now gone five consecutive games without defeat across all competitions, picking up two draws and three wins.
Congo DR have named a solid 25-man squad for October's qualifying games against Tanzania and Ethiopia, with key players like Simon Banza, Gael Kakuta, and Chancel Mbemba.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Leopards have kicked up the campaign with two wins from their opening two matches and will head into the game in search of a sixth competitive home victory since June 2022.
Tanzania has picked up four points from their opening two in the 2025 AFCON qualifying race to sit second in the standings, two points off Thursday's hosts at the top of the pole.
